
// This Hyperlambda code uses the [sockets.signal] slot to send a signal to a specified session. It includes an [args] node with three child nodes: [error] indicating an error status as true, [status] capturing the status from the [http.post] response, and [message] extracting the error message from the HTTP POST response content. This setup is useful for notifying clients about errors in HTTP POST operations.
sockets.signal:x:@.arguments/*/session
   args
      error:bool:true
      status:x:@http.post
      message:x:@http.post/*/content/*/error/*/message
